               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330905-188-person1773">
                  WILLIAM 
                  TURTON
               <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1773" type="surname" value="TURTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1773" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1773" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a groom and live at Hornsey, Mr. Bradshaw lives opposite to my master. On the 3rd of September, I saw the prisoner and another person about half-past one o'clock, in the day; the prisoner pulled off his shoes and stockings, and went into the door of Mr. Bradshaw's house - I waited about five minutes - I saw him come out and took him, with the property on him- I don't know what became of the other person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330905-188-person1774">
                  JOSEPH 
                  HICKS
               <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1774" type="surname" value="HICKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1774" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1774" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am butler to Mr. 
               <persName id="t18330905-188-person1775">
                  Joseph 
                  Hoare Bradshaw
               <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1775" type="surname" value="Hoare Bradshaw"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1775" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1775" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , he lives there, it is his dwelling-house, and is in the parish of Hornsey - I did not see the prisoner till he was in the custody of the last witness - I went up and<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183309050116"></xptr>asked him what he had got, he said, "This," and opened his apron and showed me the cruet-stand - I said, "Is this all you have?" he said, "Yes," but I found this other property in his pocket, which I had put on the sideboard in the dining-room, twenty minutes before - this cruet-stand is worth 4l. 10s., the stopper 10s., the spoon 4s., and the glasses 2s. 6d., they are all my master's - I know nothing of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18330905-188-person1776">
                  ROBERT 
                  CROUCH
               <interp inst="t18330905-188-person1776" type="surname" value="CROUCH"></interp>
